  "text": "To explore this claim, we designed a large-scale experiment with synthetic data reflecting the portfolio model found in our previous work [CITATION_1] . With synthetic data, we are able to control for data dependency and sampling, thus eliminating additional variables that affect the applicability of the statistical theory, but are not immediately relevant to this analysis. With a substantially larger statistically relevant sampling of scores, we also eliminated any small sampling effects that might have been present in the BSSR1 experiments of Section IV, where we were constrained by a well-known, but limited, data set.",
